parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the CVT transmission can cause the vehicle to hesitate, jerk, or lunge forward, leading to accidents or near-misses, especially in heavy traffic or when merging onto highways.
symptoms: The vehicle may hesitate or fail to accelerate
jerk or lunge forward
make loud noises
or vibrate excessively. In some cases
the vehicle may stall or shut off.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the concentric slave cylinder can cause the clutch pedal to stick to the floor, making it difficult or impossible to shift gears, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The clutch pedal feels soft or spongy
the clutch pedal sticks to the floor
the clutch pedal does not return to its normal position
the clutch pedal has a delayed return to its normal position
the clutch pedal has a sudden loss of pressure
the vehicle is unable to shift into gear.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the clutch master cylinder can cause the clutch pedal to stick to the floor, making it difficult or impossible to shift gears, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The clutch pedal feels soft or spongy
the clutch pedal sticks to the floor
the clutch pedal does not return to its normal position
the clutch pedal has a delayed return to its normal position
the clutch pedal has a sudden loss of pressure
the vehicle is unable to shift into gear.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the alternator can cause the battery to drain, leading to a loss of power, stalling, and increased risk of accidents.
symptoms: The battery and anti-lock braking system (ABS) warning lights illuminate
the vehicle loses power
and the engine stalls.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause the vehicle to stall, lose power, and increase the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The vehicle stalls
loses power
and warning lights illuminate on the instrument panel.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the door actuator can cause the doors to malfunction, leading to safety risks and potential theft.
symptoms: The doors do not lock or unlock properly
and the door actuator fails to function.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the clutch and transmission can cause the vehicle to stall, lose power, and increase the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The clutch pedal feels soft or spongy
the clutch pedal sticks to the floor
and the vehicle stalls or loses power.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the driver seat frame can cause the seat to shift or rock while driving, leading to a loss of control and increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The driver seat feels loose or unstable
the seat rocks or shifts while driving
the seat makes a loud creaking sound
the seat tilts or drops to one side
the seat frame breaks or fractures.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the crankshaft position sensor can cause the engine to stall, leading to a loss of power and control, which can increase the risk of an accident.
symptoms: The engine stalls
the check engine light comes on
the vehicle loses power and speed
and the vehicle may not start.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the camshaft position sensor can cause the engine to stall, leading to a loss of power and control, which can increase the risk of an accident.
symptoms: The engine stalls
the check engine light comes on
the vehicle loses power and speed
and the vehicle may not start.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission can cause the vehicle to lose power and speed, leading to a loss of control, which can increase the risk of an accident.
symptoms: The vehicle hesitates or lags when accelerating
the vehicle loses power and speed
and the transmission slips or fails to engage.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the intake air ducts/resonator can cause the engine to stall, leading to a loss of power and control, which can increase the risk of an accident.
symptoms: The engine stalls
the check engine light comes on
the vehicle loses power and speed
and the vehicle may not start.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the rear powertrain can cause the vehicle to lose power and speed, leading to a loss of control, which can increase the risk of an accident.
symptoms: The vehicle loses power and speed
the transmission slips or fails to engage
and the rear powertrain leaks oil.
